reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The stands were fantastic! Definitely will be ordering more. Perfect for those figures that don’t want to stand right. Only thing was on my female figures the hole was too small to fit on a lot of them probably because of how small the female figures feet are but I just soaked the feet in warm water and it worked. 10/10!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great with GI Joe Classified, DC and Marvel characters!
reviews.reviewText: The stands arrived fast and are of good quality. They fit perfectly on my action figures and are very sturdy. Far better than any of the stands that come in some of the packages. So far I have tested them on 3 of my collectible lines and they work perfectly. I will be buying more. I wish there was a bundle of the all black circles but the clear ones also work. Highly recommend for any collector who displays their figures.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars You Have to Stand for Something
reviews.reviewText: These are nice and solid, and the pegs feel reinforced enough that they aren't going to snap off easily. Most of the things I'm going to point out aren't really about these stands, it's about how different toy lines make their pegs.Here is the summary of action figures I've tried with these:G.I. Joe Classified - Largely CompatibleHasbro D&D Action figures - CompatibleNECA D&D Action figures - Not CompatibleMasterverse - Larger male characters compatible, female characters don't fitStar Wars Black Series - Not compatible based on the figures I triedDC Multiverse - VariesMythic Legions - The single foot round bases are compatible, single stand with two pegs not compatible

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Why are circles and rectangular same cost?
reviews.reviewText: Stands are solid, They need to be more specific in the listing. I do not like how the circle stands and the rectangle stands are the same cost for half the standing capacity. They sell them by the piece, but when ordering the 56 piece mixed bag, you get 28 pieces of each, but since you need 2 circles per figure, it feels like you get half the standing power with the circle stands. They are more versatile, but a 100% premium seems excessive.
